            </a10:author>
            <category>Videos</category>
            <category>Media Entries</category>
            <title>The basics of Total Productive Maintenance</title>
            <description>&lt;div class="watch-video-desc description"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Total Productive Maintenance (TPM) is a maintenance program which involves a newly defined concept for maintaining plants and equipment. The goal of the TPM program is to markedly increase production while, at the same time, increasing employee morale and job satisfaction.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	TPM is a innovative Japanese concept. The origin of TPM can be traced back to 1951 when preventive maintenance was introduced in Japan. However, the concept of preventive maintenance was taken from the United States. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="watch-video-desc description"&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="watch-video-desc description"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Access this 2-minute program by clicking on the link below.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
